                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210718-126-off718 t18210718-126-crimeloc721"></join>. On Sunday, the 1st of July, the prisoner lived in a house adjoining my workshop, the yard communicates with both, the things were safe the night before, and between eight and nine o'clock on Sunday night, I missed them, got an officer, went to the prisoner, and told him, I suspected he had some of my property; he denied it, and said we were welcome to search, and on searching, the officer found the property stated in the indictment; part in the room he was in, and the rest on the stairs.</p>
